From: ASK <ask@kernel-ls1046a-build>
Subject: [PATCH] tools/lib/perf: invoke Makefile.asm-headers from $(srctree)

When building libperf as a perf sub-component on arm64,
arch/arm64/kernel/Makefile.syscalls overrides the asm-headers
syscalltbl to a srctree-RELATIVE path:

    syscalltbl = arch/arm64/tools/syscall_%.tbl

(scripts/Makefile.asm-headers' default uses $(srctree)/scripts/syscall.tbl
— the arm64 override is the only in-tree caller that drops the prefix).

The libperf rule that drives this sub-make sets the output dir via
obj=$(uapi-asm) but does NOT change cwd, so when invoked from a
libperf O= path (e.g. tools/perf/libperf/) the prerequisite
arch/arm64/tools/syscall_64.tbl is looked up relative to that
unrelated directory and make fails with:

  No rule to make target '.../tools/perf/libperf/arch/arm64/include/
  generated/uapi/asm/unistd_64.h'.  Stop.
  *** [Makefile:108: uapi-asm-generic] Error 2

Pass -C $(srctree) so the relative syscalltbl prereq resolves.
The -f flag still references the absolute Makefile.asm-headers, and
obj= / target paths are absolute via $(OUTPUT), so this is a
no-behaviour-change fix for archs whose syscalltbl is already
absolute and a correctness fix for arm64.

Reproduces under bindeb-pkg's binary-perf target on linux-6.18.26.

Signed-off-by: ASK <ask@kernel-ls1046a-build>
---
--- a/tools/lib/perf/Makefile
+++ b/tools/lib/perf/Makefile
@@ -106,7 +106,7 @@
 endif
 uapi-asm-generic:
 	$(if $(syscall-y),\
-		$(Q)$(MAKE) -f $(srctree)/scripts/Makefile.asm-headers obj=$(uapi-asm) \
+		$(Q)$(MAKE) -C $(srctree) -f $(srctree)/scripts/Makefile.asm-headers obj=$(uapi-asm) \
 		generic=include/uapi/asm-generic $(syscall-y),)
 
 $(LIBPERF_IN): uapi-asm-generic FORCE
